#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring Virtual Machines"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:12
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&vmm;'s <guimenu>Details</guimenu> view offers in-depth information about "
"the &vmguest;'s complete configuration and hardware equipment. Using this "
"view, you can also change the guest configuration or add and modify virtual "
"hardware. To access this view, open the guest's console in &vmm; and either "
"choose <menuchoice> <guimenu>View</guimenu> <guimenu>Details</guimenu> </"
"menuchoice> from the menu, or click <guimenu>Show virtual hardware details</"
"guimenu> in the toolbar."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:28
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guimenu>Details</guimenu> View of a &vmguest;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:38
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The left panel of the window lists &vmguest; overview and already installed "
"hardware. After clicking an item in the list, you can access its detailed "
"settings in the details view. You can change the hardware parameters to "
"match your needs, then click <guimenu>Apply</guimenu> to confirm them. Some "
"changes take effect immediately, while others need a reboot of the "
"machine&mdash;and <systemitem>virt-manager</systemitem> warns you about that "
"fact."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:47
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To remove installed hardware from a &vmguest;, select the appropriate list "
"entry in the left panel and then click <guimenu>Remove</guimenu> in the "
"bottom right of the window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To add new hardware, click <guimenu>Add Hardware</guimenu> below the left "
"panel, then select the type of the hardware you want to add in the "
"<guimenu>Add New Virtual Hardware</guimenu> window. Modify its parameters "
"and confirm with <guimenu>Finish</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following sections describe configuration options for the specific "
"hardware type <emphasis>being added</emphasis>. They do not focus on "
"modifying an existing piece of hardware as the options are identical."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:64
#, no-c-format
msgid "Machine Setup"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:66
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section describes the setup of the virtualized processor and memory "
"hardware. These components are vital to a &vmguest;, therefore you cannot "
"remove them. It also shows how to view the overview and performance "
"information, and how to change boot options."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Overview</guimenu> shows basic details about &vmguest; and the "
"hypervisor."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:80
#, no-c-format
msgid "Overview details"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:90
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Name</guimenu>, <guimenu>Title</guimenu>, and <guimenu>Description</"
"guimenu> are editable and help you identify &vmguest; in the "
"<guimenu>Virtual Machine Manager</guimenu> list of machines."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:97
#, no-c-format
msgid "&vmguest; Title and Description"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:107
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>UUID</guimenu> shows the universally unique identifier of the "
"virtual machine, while <guimenu>Status</guimenu> shows its current "
"status&mdash;<guimenu>Running</guimenu>, <guimenu>Paused</guimenu>, or "
"<guimenu>Shutoff</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guimenu>Hypervisor Details</guimenu> section shows the hypervisor type, "
"CPU architecture, used emulator, and chipset type. None of the hypervisor "
"parameters can be changed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:121 libvirt_configuration.xml:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "Performance"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Performance</guimenu> shows regularly updated charts of CPU and "
"memory usage, and disk and network I/O."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:138
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling Disabled Charts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:139
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Not all the charts in the <guimenu>Graph</guimenu> view are enabled by "
"default. To enable these charts, go to <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
"guimenu><guimenu>View Manager</guimenu></menuchoice>, then select "
"<menuchoice><guimenu>Edit</guimenu><guimenu>Preferences</guimenu> "
"<guimenu>Polling</guimenu></menuchoice>, and check the charts that you want "
"to see regularly updated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:150
#, no-c-format
msgid "Statistics Charts"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:163
#, no-c-format
msgid "Processor"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:164
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Processor</guimenu> includes detailed information about &vmguest; "
"processor configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:169
#, no-c-format
msgid "Processor View"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <guimenu>CPUs</guimenu> section, you can configure several parameters "
"related to the number of allocated CPUs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenu
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:185
#, no-c-format
msgid "Logical host CPUs"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "The real number of CPUs installed on &vmhost;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenu
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:194 libvirt_configuration.xml:258
#, no-c-format
msgid "Current allocation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:197
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The number of currently allocated CPUs. You can hotplug more CPUs by "
"increasing this value up to the <guimenu>Maximum allocation</guimenu> value."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenu
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:205 libvirt_configuration.xml:269
#, no-c-format
msgid "Maximum allocation"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:208
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Maximum number of allocable CPUs for the current session. Any change to this "
"value will take effect after the next &vmguest; reboot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:215
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <guimenu>Configuration</guimenu> section lets you configure the CPU "
"model and topology."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:219
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When activated, the <guimenu>Copy host CPU configuration</guimenu> option "
"uses the host CPU model for &vmguest;. Otherwise you need to specify the CPU "
"model from the drop-down box."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:224
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After you activate <guimenu>Manually set CPU topology</guimenu>, you can "
"specify a custom number of sockets, cores and threads for the CPU."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:231
#, no-c-format
msgid "Memory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:232
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Memory</guimenu> contains information about the memory that is "
"available to &vmguest;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "Memory View"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenu
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:249
#, no-c-format
msgid "Total host memory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:252
#, no-c-format
msgid "Total amount of memory installed on &vmhost;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:261
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The amount of memory currently available to &vmguest;. You can hotplug more "
"memory by increasing this value up to the value of <guimenu>Maximum "
"allocation</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:272
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The maximum value to which you can hotplug the currently available memory. "
"Any change to this value will take effect after the next &vmguest; reboot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:283 libvirt_configuration.xml:289
#, no-c-format
msgid "Boot Options"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:284
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Boot Options</guimenu> introduces options affecting the &vmguest; "
"boot process."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:299
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <guimenu>Autostart</guimenu> section, you can specify whether the "
"virtual machine should automatically start during the &vmhost; boot phase."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:303
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <guimenu>Boot device order</guimenu>, activate the devices that will "
"be used for booting &vmguest;. You can change their order with the up and "
"down arrow buttons on the right side of the list. To choose from a list of "
"bootable devices on &vmguest; start, activate <guimenu>Enable boot menu</"
"guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:310
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To boot a different kernel than the one on the boot device, activate "
"<guimenu>Enable direct kernel boot</guimenu> and specify the paths to the "
"alternative kernel and initrd placed on the &vmhost; file system. You can "
"also specify kernel arguments that will be passed to the loaded kernel."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:320
#, no-c-format
msgid "Storage"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:322
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This section gives you a detailed description of configuration options for "
"storage devices. It includes both hard disks and removable media, such as "
"USB or CD-ROM drives."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:329
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding a New Storage Device"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:331
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click <guimenu>Add Hardware</guimenu> below the left panel, then select "
"<guimenu>Storage</guimenu> from the <guimenu>Add New Virtual Hardware</"
"guimenu> window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:337
#, no-c-format
msgid "Add a New Storage"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:349
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a <literal>qcow2</literal> disk image in the default location, "
"activate <guimenu>Create a disk image for the virtual machine</guimenu> and "
"specify its size in gigabytes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To gain more control over the disk image creation, activate <guimenu>Select "
"or create custom storage</guimenu> and click <guimenu>Manage</guimenu> to "
"manage storage pools and images. The window <guimenu>Choose Storage Volume</"
"guimenu> opens which has almost identical functionality as the "
"<guimenu>Storage</guimenu> tab described in <xref linkend=\"sec.libvirt."
"storage.vmm\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:363
#, no-c-format
msgid "Supported Storage Formats"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:364
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&suse; only supports the following storage formats: <literal>raw</literal>, "
"<literal>qcow2</literal>, and <literal>qed</literal>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:372
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After you manage to create and specify the disk image file, specify the "
"<guimenu>Device type</guimenu>. It can be one of the following options:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guimenu
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:379
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disk device"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:383
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>CDROM device</guimenu>: Does not allow using <guimenu>Create a disk "
"image for the virtual machine</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:389
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>Floppy device</guimenu>: Does not allow using <guimenu>Create a "
"disk image for the virtual machine</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:395
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<guimenu>LUN Passthrough</guimenu>: Required to use an existing SCSI storage "
"directly without adding it into a storage pool."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:403
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select the <guimenu>Bus type</guimenu> for your device. The list of "
"available options depends on the device type you selected in the previous "
"step. The types based on <guimenu>VirtIO</guimenu> use paravirtualized "
"drivers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:411
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the <guimenu>Advanced options</guimenu> section, select the preferred "
"<guimenu>Cache mode</guimenu>. For more information on cache modes, see "
"<xref linkend=\"cha.cachemodes\"/>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:418
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Confirm your settings with <guimenu>Finish</guimenu>. A new storage device "
"appears in the left panel."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:426
#, no-c-format
msgid "Controllers"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:428
#, no-c-format
msgid "This section focuses on adding and configuring new controllers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:433
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding a New Controller"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:435
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click <guimenu>Add Hardware</guimenu> below the left panel, then select "
"<guimenu>Controller</guimenu> from the <guimenu>Add New Virtual Hardware</"
"guimenu> window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:441 libvirt_configuration.xml:491
#, no-c-format
msgid "Add a New Controller"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:453
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select the type of the controller. You can choose from <guimenu>IDE</"
"guimenu>, <guimenu>Floppy</guimenu>, <guimenu>SCSI</guimenu>, <guimenu>SATA</"
"guimenu>, <guimenu>VirtIO Serial</guimenu> (paravirtualized), <guimenu>USB</"
"guimenu>, or <guimenu>CCID</guimenu> (smart card devices)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:462
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Optionally, in the case of a USB or SCSI controller, select a controller "
"model."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:468
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Confirm your settings with <guimenu>Finish</guimenu>. A new controller "
"appears in the left panel."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:476
#, no-c-format
msgid "Networking"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:478
#, no-c-format
msgid "This section describes how to add and configure new network devices."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:483
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding a New Network Device"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:485
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click <guimenu>Add Hardware</guimenu> below the left panel, then select "
"<guimenu>Network</guimenu> from the <guimenu>Add New Virtual Hardware</"
"guimenu> window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:503
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"From the <guimenu>Network source</guimenu> list, select the source for the "
"network connection. The list includes &vmhost;'s available physical network "
"interfaces, network bridges, or network bonds. You can also assign the "
"&vmguest; to an already defined virtual network. See <xref linkend=\"cha."
"libvirt.networks\"/> for more information on setting up virtual networks "
"with &vmm;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:513
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Specify a <guimenu>MAC address</guimenu> for the network device. While &vmm; "
"pre-fills a random value for your convenience, it is recommended to supply a "
"MAC address appropriate for your network environment to avoid network "
"conflicts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:521
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Select a device model from the list. You can either leave the "
"<guimenu>Hypervisor default</guimenu>, or specify one of <guimenu>e1000</"
"guimenu>, <guimenu>rtl8139</guimenu>, or <guimenu>virtio</guimenu> models. "
"Note that <emphasis>virtio</emphasis> uses paravirtualized drivers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:530
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Confirm your settings with <guimenu>Finish</guimenu>. A new network device "
"appears in the left panel."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:560
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling Seamless and Synchronized Mouse Pointer Movement"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:562
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you click within a &vmguest;'s console with the mouse, the pointer is "
"captured by the console window and cannot be used outside the console unless "
"it is explicitly released (by pressing <keycombo> <keycap function=\"alt\"></"
"keycap> <keycap function=\"control\"></keycap> </keycombo>). To prevent the "
"console from grabbing the key and to enable seamless pointer movement "
"between host and guest instead, add a tablet to the &vmguest;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:571
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Adding a tablet has the additional advantage of synchronizing the mouse "
"pointer movement between &vmhost; and &vmguest; when using a graphical "
"environment on the guest. With no tablet configured on the guest, you will "
"often see two pointers with one dragging behind the other."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:580 libvirt_configuration.xml:626
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:723 libvirt_configuration.xml:777
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:917
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Double-click a &vmguest; entry in the &vmm; to open its console and switch "
"to the <guimenu>Details</guimenu> view with <menuchoice> <guimenu>View</"
"guimenu> <guimenu>Details</guimenu> </menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:587
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click <guimenu>Add Hardware</guimenu> and choose <guimenu>Input</guimenu> "
"and then <guimenu>EvTouch USB Graphics Tablet</guimenu> in the pop-up "
"window. Proceed with <guimenu>Finish</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:595
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the guest is running, you will be asked whether to enable the tablet "
"after the next reboot. Confirm with <guimenu>Yes</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:602
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you start or restart the &vmguest;, the tablet becomes available in the "
"&vmguest;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:610
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding a CD/DVD-ROM Device with &vmm;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:612
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kvm; supports CD or DVD-ROMs in &vmguest; either by directly accessing a "
"physical drive on the &vmhost; or by accessing ISO images. To create an ISO "
"image from an existing CD or DVD, use <command>dd</command>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:618
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"dd if=/dev/<replaceable>cd_dvd_device</replaceable> of=my_distro.iso bs=2048"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:620
#, no-c-format
msgid "To add a CD/DVD-ROM device to your &vmguest;, proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:633 libvirt_configuration.xml:730
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Click <guimenu>Add Hardware</guimenu> and choose <guimenu>Storage</guimenu> "
"in the pop-up window."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:639
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Change the <guimenu>Device Type</guimenu> to <guimenu>IDE CDROM</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:645
#, no-c-format
msgid "Select <guimenu>Select or create custom storage</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:650
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To assign the device to a physical medium, enter the path to the &vmhost;'s "
"CD/DVD-ROM device (for example, <filename>/dev/cdrom</filename>) next to "
"<guimenu>Manage</guimenu>. Alternatively, use <guimenu>Manage</guimenu> to "
"open a file browser and then click <guimenu>Browse Local</guimenu> to select "
"the device. Assigning the device to a physical medium is only possible when "
"the &vmm; was started on the &vmhost;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:662
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To assign the device to an existing image, click <guimenu>Manage</guimenu> "
"to choose an image from a storage pool. If the &vmm; was started on the "
"&vmhost;, alternatively choose an image from another location on the file "
"system by clicking <guimenu>Browse Local</guimenu>. Select an image and "
"close the file browser with <guimenu>Choose Volume</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:674 libvirt_configuration.xml:752
#, no-c-format
msgid "Save the new virtualized device with <guimenu>Finish</guimenu>."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:679 libvirt_configuration.xml:757
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Reboot the &vmguest; to make the new device available.<phrase condition="
"\"kvm4x86\"> For more information, see <xref linkend=\"sec.libvirt.config."
"cdrom.media_change\"/>.</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:688
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding a Floppy Device with &vmm;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:690
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Currently &kvm; only supports the use of floppy disk images&mdash;using a "
"physical floppy drive is not supported. Create a floppy disk image from an "
"existing floppy using <command>dd</command>:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:696
#, no-c-format
msgid "dd if=/dev/fd0 of=/var/lib/libvirt/images/floppy.img"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:698
#, no-c-format
msgid "To create an empty floppy disk image use one of the following commands:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:704
#, no-c-format
msgid "Raw Image"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:706
#, no-c-format
msgid "dd if=/dev/zero of=/var/lib/libvirt/images/floppy.img bs=512 count=2880"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:710
#, no-c-format
msgid "FAT Formatted Image"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:712
#, no-c-format
msgid "mkfs.msdos -C /var/lib/libvirt/images/floppy.img 1440"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:717
#, no-c-format
msgid "To add a floppy device to your &vmguest;, proceed as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:736
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
