#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1292
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding a VF Network Device to an Existing &vmguest;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1293
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When the <xref linkend=\"vt.io.sriov\"/> hardware is properly set up on the "
"&vmhost;, you can add VFs to &vmguest;s. To do so, you need to collect some "
"data first."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1299
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note: The following procedure is using example data. Make sure to replace it "
"by appropriate data from your setup."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1304
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Use the <command>virsh nodedev-list</command> command to get the PCI address "
"of the VF you want to assign and its corresponding PF. Numerical values from "
"the <command>lspci</command> output shown in <xref linkend=\"sec.libvirt."
"config.io.config\"/> (for example <literal>01:00.0</literal> or "
"<literal>04:00.1</literal>) are transformed by adding the prefix \"pci_0000_"
"\" and by replacing colons and dots with underscores. So a PCI ID listed as "
"\"04:00.0\" by <command>lspci</command> is listed as \"pci_0000_04_00_0\" by "
"virsh. The following example lists the PCI IDs for the second port of the "
"Intel 82576NS network card:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1316
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.user;sudo virsh nodedev-list | grep 0000_04_\n"
"pci_0000_04_00_0\n"
"pci_0000_04_00_1\n"
"pci_0000_04_10_0\n"
"pci_0000_04_10_1\n"
"pci_0000_04_10_2\n"
"pci_0000_04_10_3\n"
"pci_0000_04_10_4\n"
"pci_0000_04_10_5\n"
"pci_0000_04_10_6\n"
"pci_0000_04_10_7\n"
"pci_0000_04_11_0\n"
"pci_0000_04_11_1\n"
"pci_0000_04_11_2\n"
"pci_0000_04_11_3\n"
"pci_0000_04_11_4\n"
"pci_0000_04_11_5"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1317
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The first two entries represent the PFs, whereas the other entries represent "
"the VFs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1323
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Get more data that will be needed by running the command <command>virsh "
"nodedev-dumpxml</command> on the PCI ID of the VF you want to add:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1328
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.user;sudo virsh nodedev-dumpxml pci_0000_04_10_0\n"
"&lt;device&gt;\n"
"  &lt;name&gt;pci_0000_04_10_0&lt;/name&gt;\n"
"  &lt;parent&gt;pci_0000_00_02_0&lt;/parent&gt;\n"
"  &lt;capability type='pci'&gt;\n"
"    &lt;domain&gt;0&lt;/domain&gt;\n"
"    &lt;bus&gt;4&lt;/bus&gt;\n"
"    &lt;slot&gt;16&lt;/slot&gt;\n"
"    &lt;function&gt;0&lt;/function&gt;\n"
"    &lt;product id='0x10ca'&gt;82576 Virtual Function&lt;/product&gt;\n"
"    &lt;vendor id='0x8086'&gt;Intel Corporation&lt;/vendor&gt;\n"
"    &lt;capability type='phys_function'&gt;\n"
"      &lt;address domain='0x0000' bus='0x04' slot='0x00' function='0x0'/"
"&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/capability&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/capability&gt;\n"
"&lt;/device&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1329
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following data is needed for the next step:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1334
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;domain&gt;0&lt;/domain&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1339
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;bus&gt;4&lt;/bus&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1344
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;slot&gt;16&lt;/slot&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1349
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;function&gt;0&lt;/function&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1356
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create a temporary XML file (for example <filename>/tmp/vf-interface.xml</"
"filename> containing the data necessary to add a VF network device to an "
"existing &vmguest;. The minimal content of the file needs to look like the "
"following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1362
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;interface type='hostdev'&gt;<co xml:id=\"sriov.iface\"/>\n"
" &lt;source&gt;\n"
"  &lt;address type='pci' domain='0' bus='11' slot='16' function='0'2/&gt;<co "
"xml:id=\"sriov.data\"/>\n"
" &lt;/source&gt;\n"
"&lt;/interface&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1365
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"VFs do not get a fixed MAC address; it changes every time the host reboots. "
"When adding network devices the <quote>traditional</quote> way with &lt;"
"hostdev&gt;, it would require to reconfigure the &vmguest;'s network device "
"after each reboot of the host, because of the MAC address change. To avoid "
"this kind of problem, libvirt introduced the <quote>interface "
"type='hostdev'</quote> directive, which sets up network-specific data "
"<emphasis>before</emphasis> assigning the device."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1377
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specify the data you acquired in the previous step here."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1384
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In case a device is already attached to the host, it cannot be attached to a "
"guest. To make it available for guests, detach it from the host first:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1389
#, no-c-format
msgid "virsh nodedev-detach pci_0000_04_10_0"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1392
#, no-c-format
msgid "Last, add the VF interface to an existing &vmguest;:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1395
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"virsh attach-device <replaceable>GUEST</replaceable> /tmp/vf-interface.xml --"
"<replaceable>OPTION</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1396
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<replaceable>GUEST</replaceable> needs to be replaced by the domain name, id "
"or uuid of the &vmguest; and --<replaceable>OPTION</replaceable> can be one "
"of the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: option
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1403
#, no-c-format
msgid "--persistent"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1406
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option will always add the device to the domain's persistent XML. In "
"addition, if the domain is running, it will be hotplugged."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: option
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1413
#, no-c-format
msgid "--config"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1416
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option will only affect the persistent XML, even if the domain is "
"running. The device will only show up in the guest on next boot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: option
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1423
#, no-c-format
msgid "--live"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1426
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option will only affect a running domain. If the domain is inactive, "
"the operation will fail. The device is not persisted in the XML and will not "
"be available in the guest on next boot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1434
#, no-c-format
msgid "--current"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1436
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option affects the current state of the domain. If the domain is "
"inactive, the device is added to the persistent XML and will be available on "
"next boot. If the domain is active, the device is hotplugged but not added "
"to the persistent XML."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1445
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To detach a VF interface, use the <command>virsh detach-device</command> "
"command, which also takes the options listed above."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1455
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dynamic Allocation of VFs from a Pool"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1456
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you define the PCI address of a VF into a guest's configuration "
"statically as described in <xref linkend=\"sec.libvirt.config.io.attach\"/>, "
"it is hard to migrate such guest to another host. The host must have "
"identical hardware in the same location on the PCI bus, or the guest "
"configuration must be modified prior to each start."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Another approach is to create a &libvirt; network with a device pool that "
"contains all the VFs of an <xref linkend=\"vt.io.sriov\"/> device. The guest "
"then references this network, and each time it is started, a single VF is "
"dynamically allocated to it. When the guest is stopped, the VF is returned "
"to the pool, available for another guest."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1472
#, no-c-format
msgid "Defining Network with Pool of VFs on &vmhost;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1473
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following example of network definition creates a pool of all VFs for "
"the <xref linkend=\"vt.io.sriov\"/> device with its physical function (PF) "
"at the network interface eth0 on the host:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1478
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;network&gt;\n"
"  &lt;name&gt;passthrough&lt;/name&gt;\n"
"    &lt;forward mode='hostdev' managed='yes'&gt;\n"
"      &lt;pf dev='eth0'/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/forward&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/network&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1479
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use this network on the host, save the above code to a file, for example "
"<filename>/tmp/passthrough.xml</filename>, and execute the following "
"commands. Remember to replace eth0 with the real network interface name of "
"your <xref linkend=\"vt.io.sriov\"/> device's PF:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1485
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"virsh net-define /tmp/passthrough.xml\n"
"virsh net-autostart passthrough\n"
"virsh net-start passthrough"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1488
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring &vmguest; to Use VF from the Pool"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1489
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following example of guest device interface definition uses a VF of the "
"<xref linkend=\"vt.io.sriov\"/> device from the pool created in <xref "
"linkend=\"libvirt.config.io.pool.host\"/>. &libvirt; automatically derives "
"the list of all VFs associated with that PF the first time the guest is "
"started."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1496
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;interface type='network'&gt;\n"
"  &lt;source network='passthrough'&gt;\n"
"&lt;/interface&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1497
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To verify the list of associated VFs, run <command>virsh net-dumpxml "
"passthrough</command> on the host after the first guest that uses the "
"network with the pool of VFs starts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1502
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;network connections='1'&gt;\n"
"  &lt;name&gt;passthrough&lt;/name&gt;\n"
"  &lt;uuid&gt;a6a26429-d483-d4ed-3465-4436ac786437&lt;/uuid&gt;\n"
"  &lt;forward mode='hostdev' managed='yes'&gt;\n"
"    &lt;pf dev='eth0'/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;address type='pci' domain='0x0000' bus='0x02' slot='0x10' "
"function='0x1'/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;address type='pci' domain='0x0000' bus='0x02' slot='0x10' "
"function='0x3'/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;address type='pci' domain='0x0000' bus='0x02' slot='0x10' "
"function='0x5'/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;address type='pci' domain='0x0000' bus='0x02' slot='0x10' "
"function='0x7'/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;address type='pci' domain='0x0000' bus='0x02' slot='0x11' "
"function='0x1'/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;address type='pci' domain='0x0000' bus='0x02' slot='0x11' "
"function='0x3'/&gt;\n"
"    &lt;address type='pci' domain='0x0000' bus='0x02' slot='0x11' "
"function='0x5'/&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/forward&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/network&gt;"
msgstr ""
